{"questionId":"9076445","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A wheel of mass 0.25 kg consists of a cylinder mounted on a central shaft. The shaft has a&nbsp;radius of 1.2 cm and the cylinder has a radius of 4.0 cm. The shaft rests on two rails with&nbsp;the cylinder able to spin freely between the rails.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4753/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_16.44.54.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/06\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The stationary wheel is released from rest and rolls down a slope with the shaft rolling&nbsp;on the rails without slipping from point A to point B.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4754/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_16.47.09.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/06.a\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>In moving from point A to point B, the centre of mass of the wheel falls through&nbsp;a vertical distance of 0.36 m. Show that the translational speed of the wheel is&nbsp;about 1 m s<sup>–1</sup> after its displacement.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>ΔKE +&nbsp;Δrotational KE = ΔGPE</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>mv</em><sup>2</sup>&nbsp;+ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em>I</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{v^2}}}{{{r^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;<em>mgh</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;×&nbsp;0.250&nbsp;× <em>v</em><sup>2</sup> +&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;×&nbsp;1.3 × 10<sup>–4</sup> ×&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{v^2}}}{{1.44 \\times {{10}^{ - 4}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.44</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;0.250&nbsp;×&nbsp;9.81 × 0.36</p>\n<p><em>v</em> = 1.2&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>m s<sup>–1</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076445","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"In moving from point A to point B, the centre of mass of the wheel falls through a vertical distance of 0.36 m. Show that the translational speed of the wheel is about 1 m s–1 afte","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.1 – Rigid bodies and rotational dynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)"